overview: The user initiated a request to evaluate their existing sleep
  questionnaire application against a Statement of Work, focusing on the need
  for a database, a client-facing dashboard, and any required authentication
  middleware. The initial codebase review revealed that while the questionnaire
  logic, PDF generation, and basic Prisma setup were in place, database storage
  for responses, CSV export, and an admin dashboard with authentication were
  missing. Through clarifying questions, it was decided to implement a simple
  password-based authentication system for the dashboard and to combine
  demographic data fields to include year of birth, sex, zipcode, weight, and
  height. A comprehensive plan was then developed, outlining the creation of a
   Prisma model, new API routes for saving and retrieving
  responses (including CSV export), a simple authentication system, and an admin
  dashboard. The implementation of this plan has just begun with the
  modification of demographic fields in the application's types, validation, and
  form components.
